<div data-bind="visible: registered() || tokenReset()">
    <h4>Hurrah! 3D printer already registered. Nothing to do here.</h4>
    <p><a href="https://www.getanywhere.io/app/devices">Go to OctoPrint Anywhere dashboard.</a></p>

    <div><small><a href="#" class="muted" onclick="$(this).children().toggleClass('icon-caret-right icon-caret-down').parent().parent().parent().next().slideToggle('fast')"><i class="icon-caret-right"></i>Not seeing your 3D printer in getanywhere.io?</a></small></div>
    <div class="hide">
        <p>Most likely it is caused by one of the following reasons:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>You logged in with a different account than the one your 3D printer was linked to. If that's the case, log out of OctoPrint Anywhere dashboard and log in with the proper account.</li>
            <li>You copied the OctoPi image from another SD card (as opposed to using original OctoPi image).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>In either case, you can solve the problem by following these 2 steps:</p>
        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span5">
                    Step 1:
                    <button class="btn btn-primary" data-bind="click: resetButtonClicked">
                        <i class="icon-spinner icon-spin" data-bind="visible: sending"></i>
                        Reset account
                    </button>
            </div>
            <div class="span5">
                    Step 2:
                    <!-- ko if: !tokenReset() -->
                        <button class="btn" disabled="true">Re-register</button>
                    <!-- /ko -->
                    <!-- ko if: tokenReset() -->
                        <a class="btn btn-primary" data-bind="attr: {href: regUrl()}" target="blank">Re-register</a>
                    <!-- /ko -->
            </div>
        </div>
        <p>If it still does not work, please <a href="mailto:support@getanywhere.io">report a bug</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class='muted'><small>Something else is wrong? Check the <a href='http://www.getanywhere.io/pub/faqs'>help page</a>.</small></div>
</div>
<div data-bind="visible: !registered() && !tokenReset()">
    <a class="btn btn-primary" data-bind="attr: {href: regUrl()}" target="blank">Register my 3D printer on getanywhere.io</a>

    <div><small><a href="#" class="muted" onclick="$(this).children().toggleClass('icon-caret-right icon-caret-down').parent().parent().parent().next().slideToggle('fast')"><i class="icon-caret-right"></i>Having difficulties registering?</a></small></div>
    <div class="hide">
      <ul>
        <li>Make sure your browser, as well as Raspberry Pi, are both connected to internet.</li>
        <li>Open a new browser window and copy this link to the address bar: <code data-bind="text: regUrl()"></code></li>
        <li>If it still does not work, please <a href="https://goo.gl/forms/bwseL3eo9G4Ra8jp2">report a bug</a>.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
</div>

